tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE Trees(
    tree_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    tree_name VARCHAR(255),
    tree_species VARCHAR(255),
    age INT,
    care_notes TEXT,
    last_checked TIMESTAMP
)

CREATE TABLE Maintenance (
    maintenance_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    tree_id INT,
    maintenance_date DATE,
    maintenace_type VARCHAR(50),
    cost DECIMAL(10,2),
    FOREIGN KEY (tree_id) REFERENCES Tree(tree_id)
);

CREATE TABLE Tree (tree_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
 tree_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
 age INT,
 species VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
 location VARCHAR(100));

CREATE TABLE MaintenanceRecord (record_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
 tree_id INT,
 maintenance_date DATE NOT NULL,
 worker_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
 maintenance_description TEXT,
 FOREIGN KEY (tree_id) REFERENCES Tree(tree_id));

CREATE TABLE TreeCareTeam (team_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
 team_lead VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
 member_count INT,
 expertise_area VARCHAR(100));

CREATE TABLE TreeCare (
        tree_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
        tree_name VARCHAR(50),
        location VARCHAR(100),
        last_trim_date DATE,
        health_status VARCHAR(20)
);

CREATE TABLE TreeMaintenance (
        maintenance_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
        tree_id INT,
        maintenance_type VARCHAR(50),
        maintenance_date DATE,
        duration_hrs INT
);

CREATE TABLE Tree (
  tree_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  tree_species TEXT,
  tree_age INT,
  planting_date DATE
)
